      "text": "Increasingly, (Wolf 2009) said, the U.S. dollar is being challenged as the currency in which oil bills are invoiced. Allegedly, according to a report in the British Independent, also by the PR China. However, in 2003, when Iraq was propagating such a departure from the oil dollar, the U.S. government had, among other things, broken off the Iraq war for this reason. "
